  <cateringDescription><![CDATA[<p>Breakfast is buffet style with a choice of cereal, bread, fresh pastries, fruits, teas, coffee and fruit juice. Guests upgrading to half board will have a three course meal with choices. </p>
<p><strong>L'Opificio Restaurant </strong>serves modern Mediterranean cuisine and a great selection of wines. There's also an a la carte menu available (payable locally). </p>
<p><strong>Attico Rooftop 225 </strong>is an exclusive restaurant and lounge bar on the roof terrace. From up here you'll have amazing views over the famous White City as far as the Adriatic Sea. There's elegant table seating as well as comfy chairs to sink into with a cocktail in hand as you watch the sun set. The a la carte menu has delicious options like fresh local fish and traditional stone-ground flour pizzas. <span>The extensive wine list offer prestigious labels as well as wines from small local producers. Normally o</span><span>pen from May to September. </span></p>]]></cateringDescription>
